cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.CV. 

The paper presents a new neural architecture, GLNs, that are well suited to online learning applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.IT (Information Theory) as the paper discusses the credit assignment mechanism and online convex optimization. The paper also presents empirical results on machine learning benchmarks, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another likely sub-category. Finally, since the paper discusses image compression as a use case for GLNs, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a possible sub-category.
